#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:510
msgid "Using the Eraser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:511
msgid ""
"The Eraser tool ( |Toonz71_076| ) allows you to partially erase lines, "
"both in vector and raster drawings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:517
msgid "Size sets the eraser size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:519
msgid ""
"Hardness sets the amount of antialiasing along the eraser border. This is"
" available for Toonz and standard raster drawings only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:521
msgid ""
"Opacity set the opacity of the eraser; passing twice on an area is not "
"considered while performing a single erasing operation, but only when "
"performing different erasing operations. This is available for raster "
"drawings only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:523
msgid ""
"Type has the options Normal, to use the standard eraser; Rectangular, to "
"perform the erasing inside the box you define; Freehand, to perform the "
"erasing inside the area you outline by clicking and dragging; and "
"Polyline, to perform the erasing inside the area you outline by defining "
"a series of lines. In vector drawings, a vector is erased only if it is "
"fully included in the area you define."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:525
msgid ""
"Mode has the options Areas, to erase only areas, Lines, to erase only the"
" drawing outline, and Lines & Areas, to perform both the operations. This"
" is available only for raster drawings."
