#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:529
msgid ""
"Invert performs the erasing on the outside of the area defined with the "
"Rectangular, Freehand or Polyline options. In vector drawings, a vector "
"is erased only if it is fully outside of the area you define."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:531
msgid ""
"Frame Range allows you to perform Rectangular, Freehand and Polyline "
"erasing on a range of frames, by defining an area in the first and then "
"in the last frame of the range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:533
msgid ""
"Pencil Mode erases lines without antialiasing, that is with jagged edges."
" This is available for Smart Raster drawings only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:537
msgid ""
"The Eraser tool ( |Toonz71_077| ) can be automatically selected by using "
"the eraser of the tablet pen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:544
msgid "Converting Raster Drawings to Vectors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:545
msgid ""
"Scanned drawings and raster ones, i.e. drawings not based on vectors, can"
" be converted into Vector-based drawings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:547
msgid ""
"Two main conversion modes are available: centerline and outline. The "
"choice between the two modes depends on which conversion best fits your "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:552
msgid ""
"In centerline mode a single vector with a variable thickness is generated"
" for each line in the drawing. This means that the converted drawing can "
"be edited like vector-based drawings made directly in Toonz, for example "
"you can change the bend of a vector with the Pinch tool ( |Toonz71_079| )"
" or with the Control Point Editor tool and the thickness with the Pump "
"tool ("
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:554
msgid "|Toonz71_080| )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:563
msgid ""
"In the outline mode two vectors are generated to define each line in the "
"drawing, and areas filled with different colors are separated by a "
"vector. This means that, for example, to change the bend of a line you "
"have to change the bend of the two vectors defining it, and to change the"
" thickness you have to model one or both vectors defining it. The "
"thickness of all the vectors is set to 0, so that they won’t be visible "
"in the final render."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:565
msgid ""
"Parameters that are not considered necessary by the user can be hidden "
"using the option button  |Toonz71_082|  at the bottom right of the "
"Convert To vector Pop Up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:569
msgid "In the Outline mode the following settings are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:571
#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:593
msgid ""
"Accuracy sets how much the vector will follow the shape of the original "
"drawing lines. High values create more precise vectors but makes them "
"more complex."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:573
msgid ""
"Despeckling removes small spots or marks from the converted images. Its "
"value expresses the size in pixels of the side of the maximum area that "
"has to be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:575
msgid ""
"Preserve Painted Areas, when activated, includes all the colors in the "
"converted level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:577
msgid "Adherence sets how much smooth curves bend toward full corners."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:579
msgid ""
"Angle sets the angular threshold below which full corners are inserted in"
" the image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:581
msgid ""
"Curve Radius sets the measure of a curve's radius below which it is "
"replaced by a smooth corner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:583
msgid ""
"Max Colors defines the maximum number of colors that are considered in "
"the raster image and used in the vector one. The value has to be set "
"taking care of the real number of colors used in the raster image. High "
"values increase the time needed for the conversion. This is relevant for "
"raster levels only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:585
msgid ""
"Transparent Color defines the color that has to be set as the transparent"
" background of the resulting vector level. This is relevant for raster "
"levels only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:587
msgid ""
"Tone Threshold sets the value of the darkest pixels to be taken into "
"account to detect lines to be converted to vectors; for low values only "
"the darkest pixels are considered thus resulting in thinner lines; for "
"high values lighter pixels are considered too, thus resulting in thicker "
"lines. This is relevant for Smart Raster levels only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:589
msgid "In the Centerline mode the following settings are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:591
msgid ""
"Threshold sets the value of the darkest pixels to be taken into account "
"to detect lines to be converted to vectors; for low values only the "
"darkest pixels are considered thus resulting in thinner vectors; for high"
" values lighter pixels are considered too, thus resulting in thicker "
"lines. For Smart Raster levels (TLV files) the process examines only "
"pixels belonging to the lines; for full-color images, pixels of the whole"
" image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:595
msgid ""
"Despeckling ignores during the conversion small areas generated by the "
"image noise; the higher the value, the larger the areas ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:597
msgid ""
"Max Thickness sets the maximum vector thickness; if this value is low "
"very thick lines will be converted in two centerline vectors defining the"
" line outline; if this value is high, they will be converted in a single "
"centerline vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:599
msgid ""
"Thickness Calibration start and end calibrates the vector thickness "
"defined according to the Threshold value; a low value will reduce the "
"vector thickness preserving its integrity. A different value inserted in "
"the Start / End field determines an animation of the thickness along the "
"length of the level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:601
msgid ""
"Preserve Painted Areas, when activated, preserves all painted areas in "
"Smart Raster levels (TLV files) and all the areas painted with colors "
"different from the line color in full-color images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:603
msgid ""
"Add Border adds a vector along the image border in order to detect also "
"areas bleeding off the image edge."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:605
msgid ""
"Enhanced Ink recognition, when activated, allows to vectorize Full color "
"images (such as TGA, TIF, PNG etc...) without antialiasing along the "
"lines. An Heuristic is used to recognize lines and painted areas creating"
" a PLI level where the lines are seen as ink and the painted areas as "
"paint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:607
msgid ""
"It is possible to select the images or the level frames that have to be "
"converted directly in the xsheet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:609
msgid ""
"When a conversion is performed a new level is created according to the "
"selection you made, and exposed in the xsheet in the column next to that "
"containing the source level: the new file has the same name of the "
"starting one but has a PLI extension, and a “v” suffix, and is saved in "
"the +drawings default folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:611
msgid ""
"Vector levels (PLI files) created with Toonz Harlequin 7.0 are not "
"compatible with previous versions of the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:613
msgid ""
"In case a PLI level with the same name already exists, the name of the "
"new file will be followed by a progressive number."
msgstr ""

