#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1458
msgid "Cloning Levels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1459
msgid ""
"Sometimes it may be useful to create a clone of a level in order to edit "
"it without affecting the original one. For example you may want to create"
" a new animation level starting from the drawings of another level, in "
"order to have two sequences similar but not identical."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1461
msgid ""
"The Clone command allows you to create a copy of the selected cells, "
"preserving the numbering order and assigning a name to the clone. The "
"_clone suffix appended to the name of the level is the default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1463
msgid ""
"The cloned level will contain only drawings exposed in selected cells, "
"even if the original level is made of more drawings; they will be "
"automatically exposed in the column on the right of the selection, "
"shifting the following columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1465
msgid ""
"The new level will be available in the scene cast as a new element; it "
"will be saved in the +drawings or +extras default folder according to the"
" format of the original file as soon as you save it with the save "
"command, or you save the scene."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1467
msgid ""
"The cell selection can also spread over several columns: in this case the"
" same number of new columns will be inserted to make room for the cloning"
" result. If more than one level is selected, the same number of new "
"levels will be created and it is not possible to assign a name to the "
"cloned levels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1469
msgid "**To clone levels:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1471
msgid "Select the cells you want to clone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/drawing_animation_levels.rst:1475
